INSERT INTO messages VALUES (225,209,3,209,15,'Fradam','i would suggest against it','certainly, if you werent equipping it, you\'d try hiding it in your pack, but if it\'s a rifle, thats going to be fairly conspicious.\r\n\r\nan affinity against guns, is an affintiy against guns -- to a town, it\'s no different to see a rifle strapped to your back, or in your hands and pointed at one of their heads.\r\n\r\nthe only reason i can think of to not go down this path, is to increase player enjoyment -- people tend to get faaaiiirly irritated when they either get killed/\"escorted out\" without their weapons.\r\n\r\nthat in turn would jus mean, players would unequip their guns before they enter a town, but as a bonus to my earlier point (it should apply even if it\'s not equipped), those players could also drop their guns outside town, and pick them up after.\r\n\r\n... so, in conclusion, i suggest against having the affinity against guns only apply on equipped items.','2001-05-10 16:39:11');
