INSERT INTO messages VALUES (601,601,4,0,15,'Fradam','hunting and other things','i was just thinking about the current methods of hunting... and i was wondering how real it was to be fighting hawks with maces?\r\n\r\ni mean, sure, you\'ve found a hawk flying about, but with me carrying a mace, just how am i going to kill it?\r\n\r\ncombat atm seems to encompass ws thrown, so perhaps im throwing my mace?\r\n\r\ni know this would bring increased complexity and such, but it\'d mean flying things could be worth more -- i.e. hawks feathers might be somehting people would be interested in when theyre small\r\n\r\nthinking about this got me thinking along some other ideas/concepts too:\r\n\r\n -- poisioning food\r\n -- something akin to a LAW, that when used can turn a piece of land into wasteland (and also killing whatever life exists in it)\r\n -- more types of cheaper armour (e.g. rubber, soft plastic)\r\n -- new methods of travelling. give the players a \"drive\" skill, and introduce new items \'skateboard\', \'roller skates\'.. etc... i know those are all only recereatinoal, but perhaps a rare find could be a sail car? it would decrease turns spent travelling. a new range of amenities can spring up around this\r\n -- new skill: beast lore/handling/ride. if you can obtain a beast of burden to use as a transport, it\'ll be useful. also, it\'s checked every now and then to keep your animals from running away from you <-- this one is important, i feel, as aside from the usual \"you\'ve left blah blah somewhere\", there\'s nothing else to depict the realism of having pets.\r\n -- this is an old idea, (i think it was random who suggested it) :: foraging for food\r\n -- new skill: guile. can be practised by conversing with bartenders/shopowners and getting away with little fibs. comes in handy if you\'re hunted down by authorities, or a towns affinity was going to kill you, you can talk your way out of it.\r\n -- roving NPCs. they might provide you with something, for example, if it was a travelling merchant, theyd be a mini version of a \'market\', or if it was an adventurer, they might challenge you on the spot.\r\n\r\nnote, i suddenly just felt full of ideas right now, so i just spilled them all out.','2001-05-19 06:31:36');
