INSERT INTO messages VALUES (815,797,3,810,1,'Rizen','i\'m glad you said that','cuz now i can ask the really important question\r\n\r\n<h1>WHY?!?</h1>\r\n\r\nwhat was in pre-sotf quid that isn\'t in this quid? i want to make this quid as cool as possible, but i don\'t know what i\'ve missed. this quid has all the stuff the old quid did (as far as i can remember). and best of all, xanthii and some of the others are coming back to this quid.','2001-05-29 09:49:14');
INSERT INTO messages VALUES (816,797,3,815,8,'randomsyllable','OOC: why','I\'m probably the wrong person to be talking about this, seeing how little time is was in before it shifted....\r\n\r\nhowever:\r\n\r\nThere was still a better sense of community, i think. There was always a set goal: to become a quidder. However, to accomplish that goal, you had to be active on the site, share art or stories, and post messages. Now all you need to do is win a monthly game.\r\n\r\nThere was also a far better sense of competition. I remember asking about the dEity (highest karma total, i believe). There were clans and characters. As well, there was no domination on the game. Just on interaction. So far in this quid, at least half the posts are about SotF. There were no long posts that I read in the old quid about dE. There were just people enjoying themselves.\r\n\r\nThats just me though.\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nJust some thoughts.','2001-05-29 14:39:28');
INSERT INTO messages VALUES (817,783,4,790,15,'Fradam','an idea','might be to allow a one square radius for shouting?\r\n\r\nshouting is rather loud (or so i\'ve heard), and when it says \"shouting done\", it could say \"shouting done, and Racer X has left the area.\"\r\n\r\nyou could even make it comical -- \"Shouting done, and because of your foul stench, Racer X left in a hurry.\"','2001-05-29 16:36:08');
INSERT INTO messages VALUES (818,804,2,807,19,'Dinsdale','OOC-EEEGoRRRRRRRR!!!!!','DAMN YOU!!!! SHUT UP, ASSJERK!!! I SAID SERIOUS!!!\r\n______________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________\r\n~totally ignoring EEEEGoR, Dins waits for Racer to reply....~','2001-05-29 16:36:25');
INSERT INTO messages VALUES (819,797,3,816,15,'Fradam','OOC: too right, friar syllable','random\'s pretty much summed it up.\r\n\r\nthe goals of this quid are different to the old, and thus, conversation is heavily twistes. i mean, it\'s all ivor, dins, kurt, and racer and bishop do to jus keep bar brawl active, much less the serious quid discussions of old.\r\n\r\ni thikn there\'s a certain lacking of maturity to keep that sort of thing going in quidspeak -- probably because the avergae age of posters is under 14. i mean, in old quid, there was walla who was 12, but it was heavily balaned out, by sane, calm people like Ring, Fyth, and Val, who kept their own people in line.\r\n\r\nevan the ill-fated evanmoore, who is off on his glorious quest to write an rpg which he believes can compete with dE without marketting it over the web, brought a certain element of maturity to the dicussion at quid.\r\n\r\neveryone\'s favourite mum, seth, even, had a soemwhat stronger sense of mental maturity than what exists today, and that too contributed to the discussions of old.\r\n\r\nthat level of maturity, is what made quid special -- kids always want to be adults, and for he most part, those who are left an try to keep quid going, are the kids of dE. when there are no more adults to play with -- no more people who IRL are more powerful+bigger+tougher -- the fun begins to subside, as you cant look them squarely in the eye and talk to them on a one-to-one basis.\r\n\r\ni just hope we can bring the old guys back to quid, because that level of community was set in place by them intially (at my entrance).\r\n\r\ngranted, a lot of this is because Quid is now a reward to free-wheeling SotFers (who are for the most part, young and immature), as opposed to dedicatted karma-gaineers, who can be cheap, at times, but know where the game starts and stops, because they are all players of deadEarth.\r\n\r\n<b>steps off the soapbox</b>','2001-05-29 16:46:01');
