INSERT INTO messages VALUES (833,797,3,830,10,'Bishop','my two cents','(how many times did we see that topic in pre sotf dE?)\r\n\r\nanywho....\r\n\r\ni think this quid over the other sotf one,\r\n\r\nand dum dum dum the old quid over this.\r\n\r\ni think everyone is fooling themselves trying to fabricate a sense of community.  The old community came about over time.  Its impossible to build a true community, it is an entity in itself that needs nurturing and constant evolution.  \r\n\r\nThe reason it was so good back then was simple,  clans.  When clans left the site i believe thats when the \"community\" got sucked away.  THe old quid discussions, running straight down clan lines, the role play, the banter, the quick wit and counter wit, without clans we are all just a group of individuals.  Fine, but a community is formed when people come together,  there is little doing that now.  (Well in comparison to the old days *sigh*)\r\n\r\nRiz, youve done a top notch job, i firmly believe that it is only a matter of time before firstly the dE site has the same sense of community, and barring wankers like trader, here as well.\r\n\r\n\r\nOne suggestion though,  perhaps make quidnunce a shared board between deadearth and sotf for a while.  That way any non that wins this great game of yours may be put on to dE by us old heads.\r\n\r\nThat and you can keep giving us those grat stories.   (Dammit man i want to hear about noz in oz)\r\nthat rhymes and i know it','2001-05-29 22:03:26');
