INSERT INTO messages VALUES (931,931,5,0,11,'Eeeegor','ATTN: NARX','Listen, and listen well. \r\n\r\nHeed my words, all who decide to align themselves with NARX, or any attempt to destroy Racer X, as an individual, will be dealt with by myself.  Twice I have won SotF, and you would do well not to try me.  Not only will you have me to deal with, you will have the inhabitants of Quidnunc Tavern to tackle.\r\n\r\nIf you know what is good for you, you WILL desist in your current activities.\r\n\r\nEeeegor - <i>Twice winner of SotF, and the greatest winner yet</i>','2001-06-02 05:17:06');
INSERT INTO messages VALUES (932,932,3,0,111,'Xanthii','OOC: Look what the cat drug in','First of all, I want to thank Rizen for the invitation. It couldn\'t come at a better time, actually. The folks running coolboards have been bought by another company and decided (rather rudely, I thought) that they will be suspending service at the end of this month...so Ninth Gate will be homeless. (sigh) \r\n\r\nThe storyboard is going to reflect something a little less mundane, to be sure. Perhaps the upstairs neighbors decide to retaliate? It may be going out, but it will go out with a megaton blast, to be sure.\r\n\r\nQuestions I\'m hearing from my gamers are: Was the invitation for all those on the board, or just those who used to be in the Quid?\r\n\r\nReason I ask is that if it was only for former quidders, Marcus will probably just relocate the tavern to Gamers.com so that Rish can run her game.\r\n\r\nEither way, we\'re gonna miss a few of the perks like posting in full html...pop up profiles and character sketches that have the option of showing on each post. (hint hint) Who knows...maybe Rizen would like to help us there? :)\r\n\r\nXan\r\n\r\n\r\n','2001-06-02 08:40:19');
INSERT INTO messages VALUES (933,797,3,797,111,'Xanthii','OOC: Th\' kitt\'n speaks','Technically speaking, the board seems faster and threads are orderly on the full list. \r\n\r\nI saw a \"next thread\" link but not a \"next message\" link. Better yet, it would make it a bit easier to follow if the messages were on the same page...(that way we could just scroll down to see the next message in the thread, instead of waiting for another whole page to load for each message). Something similar to the setup on Gamers.com. Just my 2 cents.\r\n\r\nAs far as content? I really haven\'t read through everything yet. (I just got here) but it looks mostly ooc, to me...and tho it\'s necessary when we want to talk as ourselves... it does (just by nature of the interruption) have a tendency to kill the \"flow\" of any freeform interaction going on. People need to \"switch gears\" and sometimes when they do, the creative spark fizzles. No ones fault, just human nature.\r\n\r\npre-SotF Quid moved fast. If you missed a day, you missed a LOT of action. Hell, if you missed posting for two hours, your kill could be barbequeing before you even have time to field strip it! (remember Seamus\' gator?? hehe)\r\n\r\nLastly, through reading what I have so far, I see a lot of reference to the \"old community\" and it makes me a little teary. It\'s nice to know us ol\' folx were missed. (sniff) We really thought that no one cared for our opinions or how we would like to see the game go, and it\'s nice to see that we were wrong.\r\n\r\nXan','2001-06-02 09:05:43');
