INSERT INTO messages VALUES (948,934,5,934,4,'stroker ace','hakuna matada','nothing wrong with that, dont know why you guys are trying to stick up for each other anyway...you know as well as i racer problably deserves it...one day i seen him kill the same newbie 3 times in a row, the guy was still wet behind the ears...just trying to learn how to play...you know he didnt have no good equipment...racer just did it to watch the kid rack up a bunch of turns just to bend him over...yeah you know your a real man when you slay someone who doesnt know the difference between a good set of starting skills and selling your quite useless projectile weapons when you start to boost a few other skills...stirring things up is what this board is about...dont tell them to relax, tell them to go fuck themselves...and i dont care if you kill me or not, anybody who has to have someone else to speak for them is a beotch anyway...oh and you guys dont have to post a snappy retort as i am quite aware of the hipocrosy in what i said...if it means they are problably coming after me later anyway, i dont hesitate. just dont go and massacre all the newbloods just because you can...although it is kinda fun watching all the names dissapear from the ranks...all im sayin is that i thought doughboys message was at least something original and more likely trying to be more humourous than vengeful...let the newbloods at least get used to the water before you kill them 10 times in a row...think of it this way fellow outlaws, small fish dont do much of anything for you but a chance at being lynched, and all for what? a frickan goat-skin shawl... some fresh minds posting new messages is always good ... i am by no means trying to start a beef with any of you...it is just something i have been pondering for a while (because you can catch more flys with honey than with vinegar)...i was just waiting for a good example...trash talk, its kinda like salt and pepper, you add it for flavor...newbies say some interesting shit sometimes...remember we were all new once, i cant believe you pros would even take the time to respond to a new guy who is a little peaved because he keeps getting killed by the same person for just trying to learn the game...we have all been there, done that, and most likly made threats because we didnt know what was up...until you learn the game it is all about trial and error anyway...error usually resulting in you having to start over...so all im saying is lighten up a little, let the newbies learn the game...then when they get cocky, lay the smack-down straight-up...dont let them know in the message boards whos attention they got (you could have just ruined a perfectly good ambush)...they get your name and it is just gonna alert them of your interest...you can always give them a \"u just bit into a shit-sandwich\" shout before you crush them flat anyway...why not show your expert tactics by helping the new player out for a change...newbies wont forget who dropped them a few things...oh wait that would be inconceavable because you learned by the fist...nobody gets a free ride to the top anyway...and even with the little stuff you give them...they still have to get past their newbie status...because i know if i aint gettin first place after months of play(actually i had it once for about 5 minutes) then jonny-on-the-spot damn sure wont either....remember, it is just a game....or are we unknowingly participating in possible government test scenarios for after WWIII happens?...thats a joke...even though im not laughing...','2001-06-02 23:45:16');
