INSERT INTO messages VALUES (997,965,3,987,111,'Xanthii','Xanthii smiles a bit...','...at the banter between Fradam and Eeeegor. She\'s missed this. The past week on the road left her hungering for the sound of another even vaguely human voice. She is worried about her friends...especially Rish. Closing her eyes briefly she tries to block out that particular pain. Perhaps drowning her misery in glass upon glass of alcohol was not the answer, but it would at least make the situation bearable -- if only for the time it took her to sober up and start again. \r\n\r\nShe moves a hand to her pocket and withdraws a small metal bracer with a red stone. Dimly within, the stone glows. Whereever she was, Rish still lived. Xanthii is sure of it. But for how long? With that dismal thought, she wipes a tear and accepts another glass of scotch.\r\n\r\n\"I\'ve no more to say, my friend. I was the only one left when the vortex cleared. For all I know, they are the ones who lived and I\'m in Hell talking to you all.\"\r\n\r\nThe golden streaks in Xanthii\'s hair shift to a deeper hue.\r\n\r\n\"Tell me your tale. You\'ll have a captive audience in me, for after this glass I\'m quite sure I\'m going nowhere...\"','2001-06-04 11:39:22');
INSERT INTO messages VALUES (998,931,5,989,175,'im6re6ory','Then I agree...','to disagree.  Your loyalty is commendable, though perhaps unmerited in some cases.  Nietzche said \"Gratuity is a disease of dogs.\"  This surely applies to many of you.  \r\nI prefer this other one of his \"Whoever fights monsters should see to it that in the process he does not become a monster. And when you look long into an abyss, the abyss also looks into you.\"  This is what stroker ace is referring to, and I wholeheartedly agree.  \r\nInterestingly enough, Nietzche also said that madness in an individual is rare, but in groups, families, nations, religions, and races it is the rule.  And you thought I didn\'t understand...','2001-06-04 11:39:44');
