INSERT INTO messages VALUES (1042,931,5,1000,10,'Bishop','interesting...','but how can it be implemented,  the crimson terror is something that no one is meant to be able to kill, and by allowing and sam, terrence or sally to become one IMHO would upset the balance of the game.  Also te game does not reall support that sort of interaction i mean the monsters you have spoken of are not driven by hunt/scavenge/sneak etc.\r\n\r\nthey are hunt/kill animals. If you wish to be like that then there is ample opportunity to do that as a human.  I like that quote about not becoming a monster after hunting monsters.  But a monster must be defined by not asthetics but its thought.  This game gives you every opportunity as it is to play a monster.\r\n\r\nthank you for your time','2001-06-05 17:41:38');
INSERT INTO messages VALUES (1043,896,1,1039,175,'im6re6ory','Bishop is right...','I don\'t think there is a problem with the cost of anything.  After a few \"ventures in capitalism\" and I have plenty of food and $tandards.  I do well as a post-apocalyptic day trader.  As for it being too easy, I am not convinced.  It is easy for me, but it doesn\'t seem to have caught on.  This is one way for pacifistic survivors to get ahead.\r\nThe Domestics idea is a good one.  There should be a factor such as that to control the survivability of food.','2001-06-05 17:58:19');
