INSERT INTO messages VALUES (1064,932,3,1024,111,'Xanthii','RE: Ninth Gate Tavern','That is a wonderful gesture...one that I\'ll gladly take you up on...that is if you still feel up to it after you finish reading this...hehe.\r\n\r\nI do understand your wanting to keep Quid to a select few, I just thought since the invitation was visible to everyone at the Ninth Gate...you might have wanted all of us...\r\n\r\nUnfortunately, I really don\'t see any of them having any inclination to play SotF to win their way in -- no offense, but if I had to, I probably wouldn\'t either...just based on simple time restrictions. If I were a kid with nothing better to do, maybe, but I have a full time job, two children, as well as a side business. If given the choice of mudding or freeforming...I\'d pick the latter. Less stressful, more relaxing and creative, and if my mundane body needs to be elsewhere for a few hours (sleeping, working), I don\'t need to worry about some lil runt coming by and killing me ;) \r\n\r\nAs to the location...I think the new dE site would be better. The Ninth Gate really has nothing to do with SotF and everything to do with the actual roleplaying game -- so it would \"fit\" better.\r\n\r\nBesides: A general admission \"In Character\" freeform area would be a retreat for those who don\'t like computer games, but still want to be active with dE...\r\n\r\nRestrictions on membership? I had none before and had no problems. I\'d say to let it be open to anyone with a dE account, providing they play by the basic freeform guidelines (I could supply this)\r\n\r\nFeatures that would be really nice are a moderator mode that would allow the blocking of a poster who gets out of hand...and perhaps the ability to make a post visible or invisible. \r\n\r\nThis is useful when someone posts something that is \"questionable\" due to bad timing, character referred to isn\'t there, posting about another characters reactions without their permission...etc., giving the moderator time to contact the poster to correct, delete, or modify the post without having to out and out delete it. Sort of like moving it back to \"preview mode\".\r\n\r\nQuestion, can you edit a post that is already posted? If not, that would be nice, too. :)\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n','2001-06-06 17:47:52');
