INSERT INTO messages VALUES (1161,1121,3,1121,10,'Bishop','OOC:  woooooo riz youdaman','Firstly it was Godsbane that was the pro mutant clan.\r\n\r\nSecondly yes bring back the clans.....\r\n\r\nI think start back the old clans,  set a \"clan leader\", its then their responsibility to write the stories of their clan outlining, their manifesto, these stories are told by the bartenders in towns,  this will give the nons a fair idea of who is who.  Once the nons are slowly getting the idea across, us quidders who kow about these things can push the idea,  Dont broadcast the dis/advantages of being in a clan just say that it will give you an overall advantage then playing without a clan.\r\n\r\nFinally get the clan leaders to determine what sort of initiation there can be. Perhaps the people that want to be in a clan must track down the clan leader in game and ask to join.  Then the clan leader can see their sotf history, (#pks #thefts etc) and determine whether or not they are suitable for the clan.\r\n\r\nAfterall we dont just want people being in a clan for the bonus, we want them in the clan RPing the clan.  I mean I wouldnt want Wraiths running around pking, its not who we are.\r\n\r\n\r\nAs for the abilities and stuff...\r\n\r\nGive godsbane automatic mutant status, start them with a certain amount of rads and perhaps a certain fear factor - if they are attacked or attack a non-mutant they get a combat bonus. \r\n\r\nFDP - some resistance to radiation (anyone remember their anti rad serum?) And perhaps due ot doctor valarkin a hihger than normal first aid which gives them the abiity to void poison from their or others bodies.\r\n\r\nFamily - immune from theft/murder retribution from towns.  Some level of theft/attacking within the clan (they are a crime family afterall its in their blood right?) But then perhaps as a negative an affinity against for being known criminals.\r\n\r\nNull - give\'m a senses bonus, and perhaps a \"null weapon\" at creation that is a pretty powerful weapon.  As disadvantages... i dont know, perhaps if they attacka wraith they automatically lose (they always did:) )\r\n\r\nAlphaPrime:  THis is tough because i never read anything about your clan riz, but instead of no pking, perhaps your newbie status is raised to say 4 or 6 thousand.  I really couldnt say.\r\n\r\nNow my beloved wraiths....\r\nI guess the only thing that is really applicable is better weapons and armour at creation.  However if that was it then who would want to be a wraith? i mean its only a matter of time before you can get better armour and weapons...\r\n\r\nThe inital wraiths - (while they were still a power controlled unit) were selected for their special abilities in a field, so perhaps the skill of choice being higher is a possiblity.\r\n\r\nAs disadvantages greater chance of governmental retribution on theft/murder (its not who we are)\r\nA negative comabt modifier for attacking a \"family\" member.  anyone? its hard to assign disadvantages to yourself.\r\n\r\nThen make interclan relations...\r\ngodsbane - only pks against other muties are considered pks\r\nNull - wraith kills are not counted towards pktotal\r\nWraiths - the reciprocal but family kills are counted double\r\nFamily - well ill let them say what they think is appropriate here.\r\n\r\n\r\nThankyou riz, i am very excited.\r\n','2001-06-09 19:43:12');
