INSERT INTO messages VALUES (1166,1121,3,1161,15,'Fradam','OOC: good stuff','RE: FDP\r\n\r\nwhilst, in the end aside from EM and his creativity, the FDP was the most numerous of all clans (and still in one clan)\r\n\r\nRE: abilities\r\n\r\nive done some thinking about this, and the concept of allocating a certain amount of terrirty (its towns/villages.. no cities, i think.. thats too much), based on what people remember of their RP-ing experiences\r\n\r\nheres\' what i remember -- wraiths controlling large portions of QLD, the Family owning the underside of North Sydney, the FDP controlling denver, and looking to liberate another city (or was it the other way round?), Null having a junkyard.\r\n\r\nso with that in mind:\r\n\r\n<li>i dont think, unless hagness returns, that we should reserruct godsbane in this.\r\n\r\n<li>FDP -- increased shielding. give them a few towns, all with doctors.\r\n\r\nthe problem, is that none of their members are around, so we dont have the majority of their info. i know hagness gamed with a few of them occasionally, but aside from that, theres nobody else around to tell the stories.\r\n\r\n<li>Family -- because people dont like us, increase the cost of goods (signifcantly). give us one average town and since we fence, it should be fitted with a trade depot.. \r\n\r\ngiving us an immunity to theft is fine. the immunity to murders, though, might be going a little far -- it depends on how you (rizen) deal with the whole PK issue on at the moment.\r\n\r\n<li> a few scrapyards only Null members can scavnge from? a bonus to senses, obviously, and as bishop suggested, one unique item (only can be carried/used by Null members)\r\n\r\n<li> AlphaPrime -- i did some thinking about your clan riz, and i think rather than bishops suggestion, you put it the other way round. after all, then you guys would be \"newbies\" for a long time, sorta indicating you were \'dumb\"/\"inexperienced\", which ofcourse isnt the impressin we want from the first and oldest clan.\r\n\r\nmy suggestion, is to make it so other players can only steal/attack from AlphaPrime once they\'re apssed, say 6k/8k turns. in other words, you have to be fairly good to mix with you guys =)\r\n\r\n<li>wraiths -- give them a number of average-sized towns/villages.\r\n\r\nhaving a clan being in control of a town/village could entail the following\r\n\r\n<li> a higher chance of other clans being kicked out/killed/etc etc for doing anything in the town\r\n<li> only stories by the afifiliated clan to be told by bartender\r\n<li> slightly less costs\r\n<li> less chance of bad random town events\r\n<li> more chance of good random town events\r\n<li> free room rental\r\n\r\nand well, for interclan relations, it all sounds good\r\n\r\ni guess for the family, you could say that nobody likes us very much, and that murders/thefts against unaligned people (solo players) arent counted towards the total\r\n\r\nim all up for this riz, thanks =)','2001-06-09 23:59:58');
INSERT INTO messages VALUES (1167,1121,3,1166,15,'Fradam','ooops','forgot disadvantages for the other clans\r\n\r\n<li>Null -- since they like going into things headstrong where the odds are impossible (5 on 2), give them a combat bonus when attacking things that seem impossible, enough to give them a chance.. not to the point of ridiculous\r\n\r\nfor example, currently a 14-15 combat is needed to take out a bear.. if a Null member had a 12-13 combat and tried attacking, their bonus would make em about 14-15\r\n\r\nhowever, if they were 2-3, their bonus should only be up to 9-10\r\n\r\nsomething on the order of a sliding scale, if you get me?\r\n\r\n<li> FDP -- not strong enough advantage to warrant a disadvntage\r\n\r\n<li> AlphaPrime -- well, its jus you and vrby, isnt it? neither of you can shout to anybody (since you\'re so elite, hehe)\r\n\r\n','2001-06-10 00:10:30');
INSERT INTO messages VALUES (1168,1121,3,1167,6,'Kurtillius','00C- Ouch! No shouting??','Now that would hurt!!\r\n\r\nI like the suggestions for all the clans Fraddy, but I don\'t think we should do the Null item one.. I mean, we\'d start with an item that would be useless once we got a better weapon, and that advantage would be rendered obselete. Perhaps if you made it so that once a Null hit, say, 10K turns, the Null Flaming Cattle Prod would be added to their inventory, implying that they made it over time, and then make the weapon slightly better than the .50, to make the perk worthwile...\r\n\r\nAnd also, I, personally, don\'t really like the thought of clan controlled cities. I mean, it\'s realistic for Wraiths and Family, but I doubt clans like Null and Alphaprime (having read the old stuff) would really control entire towns.','2001-06-10 00:56:55');
