INSERT INTO messages VALUES (1172,1121,3,1168,1,'Rizen','not getting it','ok. i\'ve read all of the suggestions that have been presented here, and though i like them, i must say that on the whole it seems that most of you aren\'t getting the idea. \r\n\r\n1) clans in sotf has nothing to do with clans in dE other than i want to immortalize the names of some of the original popular dE clans.\r\n\r\n2) we will be bringing back the clans system on the dE site at some point, so as far as all your story telling and stuff goes, you\'ll have a place for that.\r\n\r\n3) there cannot be clan leaders or initiation, or any other such nonsense in sotf. the fact is that you guys come and go, and sotf cannot be dependant on individuals for such an important function.\r\n\r\n4) there will be only one bonus per clan, and we\'d like to make that bonus something that sticks with, and is useful to the character for it\'s entire existance. this means that giving the players a cool weapon, or something to that effect probably won\'t cut it. instead, some of the other bonuses (like immunity to gov\'t) is something that does stay with the character throughout it\'s life.\r\n\r\nin short, <i>sotf != de</i>. \r\n\r\nhowever, after reading many of your posts, i can see the need for a political structure around the clans. therefore, i propose that this will be the future of the clans system in sotf:\r\n\r\n1) each clan shall have one bonus and no negatives added to them. (clans and bonuses yet to be decided).\r\n\r\n2) each player shall be able to select a clan or choose to go clanless at character creation, and only at character creation.\r\n\r\n3) at the government building (which will be added when we add the new bank system) each member of a given clan shall be able to pledge themselves to a person in the clan, thus making the highest ranking member of the clan, the clan leader.\r\n\r\n4) if any member of any clan does a wrong against their own, word of the deed shall be leaked out throught gossip system in the taverns. no other punishment shall occur. the clansmen can then take it upon themselves to deal with their clanmate as they see fit.\r\n\r\nwhat say you?','2001-06-10 02:37:38');
INSERT INTO messages VALUES (1173,1070,3,1150,1,'Rizen','that may be possible','but what will happen is that we\'ll add backpacks and stuff to the game, then lower the total limit of what you can carry to less than 500, and the back packs might bring you up to 500. be careful what you wish for.','2001-06-10 02:39:41');
INSERT INTO messages VALUES (1174,1137,1,1162,1,'Rizen','understand this','1) if it were up to me (and most of the TGC staff) we\'d make sotf a much more brutal world. probably even more brutal than the dE world.\r\n\r\nhowever, the reality is that we need to eat. therefore we need to make money on sotf. that means that we must make considerations for players who are not yet ready for the brutalness of this world. \r\n\r\ntherefore, the banking system will allow you to store exactly 3 items. those three items can sit there between characters, and it does not matter what the three items are. it could be 3 standards or a piece of armor, a weapon, and a ration. this is a small concession to make to open up the world of sotf to those who aren\'t quite prepared to deal with it.','2001-06-10 02:44:38');
