INSERT INTO messages VALUES (1812,1565,3,1566,111,'Xanthii','Should this even be an issue?','What Rizen stated was:\r\n\"From this point forward any member of Quidnunc Tavern has the right to make a recommendation for the future of Quidnunc Tavern, deadEarth, and SotF.\"\r\n\r\nHow I read this, he is looking for recommendations for the future of the physical representations of the tavern, dE and SotF -- not recommendations regarding current inhabitants of said places and whether or not they add/detract from the Quid experience.\r\n\r\nI can understand voting \"in\" someone who has not \"earned\" their entry through standard means, but voting someone \"out\" based on activity or lack thereof? There is nothing in the rules that states a person must make \"X\" posts a week to maintain their presence here. \r\n\r\nOuting is a punishment that insinuates the person has committed a severe rules infraction...but if there is no rule, there is no infraction; therefore, nothing upon which to vote.\r\n\r\nHorse before the cart.\r\n\r\nWhat you could do, for example, is make a suggestion that rules for conduct be enstated for the Quid that involve minimum participation requirements. \r\n\r\nTHAT would be votable.\r\n\r\nOf course, since there is no provision for minimum participation currently, this proposal would (to be fair to all concerned) have to be emailed to those Quid members who do not read the board daily, who otherwise may miss the opportunity to vote it out.\r\n\r\nMy thoughts\r\n\r\nXanthii\r\n\r\n','2001-07-04 20:09:14');
INSERT INTO messages VALUES (1813,1606,3,1733,111,'Xanthii','Proposal - Squireship','I propose, as a requirement for unearned entry into the Quid, a Squire (trial) period of one month.\r\n\r\nSo for example, if I were to want someone in, I would stake my reputation on the worthiness of my Squire -- who if he screws up while under duty to me in his trial month (i.e., doesn\'t follow the rules), Rizen could oust not only the Squire, but me as well.\r\n\r\nIt would take a LOT to put that much on the line for a friend...and if a person did, I know I would be more willing to vote their Squire in -- based on the faith they must have in them to risk their OWN entry to the Quid.\r\n\r\nI will vote yes, if there is someone willing to Squire this individual.\r\n\r\n','2001-07-04 20:25:29');
INSERT INTO messages VALUES (1814,1606,3,1813,5,'Racer X','I can see your point...','but I just don\'t think that anyone should be kicked out of Quid at someone else\'s fault. I mean, if you got kicked out of Quid because someone else did something wrong, it just doesn\'t make sense. Everyone makes mistakes, and therefore, others should not be to blame. We all worked to be in here, and should not be ousted because of someone else\'s small mistake(s).\r\n\r\nIf we were ever to do something like that, I think it should simply be the person on their own. No need to bring anyone else in this. We give them something to do, and if they fail, we could still vote them in as we see fit. Effort counts. Not the mistakes.','2001-07-04 21:40:44');
INSERT INTO messages VALUES (1815,1749,2,1809,10,'Bishop','A dusty Akurba...','appears from the pit, it plops onto the ground sending a little cloud of dust flying.  Moments later Bishop can be seen clawing his way up the pits wall with two, foot long daggers.  He drags himself out of the hole and collapses in a heap clutching his ribs.  Blood flows from his mouth, and begins to pool.  Bishops chest heaves, he raises his eyes to Ringleader...  \"You are gonna regret that little man\"\r\n\r\nBishop drags his broken body to where his hat lays.  Mustering al his energy he rocks up onto his haunches, propping himself up with his longsword. Reaching into his coat he pulls out a rusty old hip flask. Throwing his head back Bishop gulps down the last of his scotch. It burns his throat and sends a shiver up his spine.\r\n\r\nReplacing the daggers in their sheathes on Bishops calves, bishop tries to lift his longsword...','2001-07-04 22:08:11');
