INSERT INTO messages VALUES (2051,2028,5,2033,447,'Slender','Flaw','Fradam, \r\n\r\nFlaw is in the game, as I said, not in my play. Ideally, the optimal strategy for \"winning\" should not be boring.  Let\'s move this part of the discussion to Game Discussion.\r\n\r\nRacer X,\r\n\r\n   Lets keep the trash here :)  \r\n\r\nSure, the butt kicking was mutual.  But we\'ve never done a full month without someone deciding that an alliance \"wasn\'t silly after all\".\r\n\r\nThis month, I\'m gonna try and \"win\".  \r\n\r\nYawn.\r\n\r\nNext month (assuming I\'m successful, which is of course not guaranteed) I\'ll have a different goal.  \r\n\r\nAnd someone better get out a mop with a LONG handle, cuz there\'s going to be blood on the ceiling.','2001-07-08 18:46:18');
INSERT INTO messages VALUES (2052,1899,1,2041,15,'Fradam','okay, so rizen','slender\'s made an interesting point\r\n\r\nhe believes it\'s a flaw in the game, that the optimal strategy for winning, is dead boring.\r\n\r\nwhat say you?','2001-07-08 19:00:39');
INSERT INTO messages VALUES (2053,2053,1,0,447,'Slender','Optimal Strategy','It looks to me like that the optimal strategy for winning the game, in it\'s current form, is to \r\n\r\n1) Get a viable character\r\n2) Join alphaprime, to make ourself less of a target.\r\n3) Bang out as many moves as possible, hoping that you don\'t get hit with random attacks.\r\n\r\nI invite others to present _any_ strategy more likely to get a high move-count.  At the same time, this is pretty damn boring.  More on that later.\r\n\r\nI asert that the optimal strategy for \"winning\" a game should not be boring.  Do you have any ideas about what the Powers that Be could do that would make things better?\r\n\r\nSome possiblities:\r\n \r\n1) Eliminate alphaprime.\r\n2) Add a moves bonus (5K, 8K, 10K?) for rubbing out another character.\r\n3) Change the victory conditions away from number of moves.\r\n','2001-07-08 19:03:32');
