INSERT INTO messages VALUES (2183,2162,3,2181,447,'Slender','On further reflection...','I figure that it would be better if the affinity had a \r\n\r\n 1) 25% chance of getting applied \r\n 2) got applied _just after_ the interaction\r\n\r\nThis would mean that no-one could pull a complete Alphaprime by camping in a murder affinity area, and that no place would be really safe from Quidders.\r\n\r\nBut it would also mean that you would really have to _want_ to go in there to get someone camped put there.\r\n\r\nAlthernatively, the affinty check could always be done (as I first proposed) but the nature of the afinity check could change, so that affinity only kicks in 25% (or 50%, or whater) of the time.\r\n\r\nEven more complex schemes have the chance of affinity applying \r\nbe based on stealth characteristic...\r\n\r\nHeck, ofr all I know it already is based on the stealth characteristic.\r\n\r\nGuess I\'m gonna have to do some experiments...\r\n\r\nOr I could just hack into the Aplhaprime mainframe, and check the sources...','2001-07-10 10:56:59');
