INSERT INTO messages VALUES (2189,2120,3,2173,447,'Slender','Renown is just...','...code for a more complex method of scoring, it sounds like.  \r\n\r\nThe current method of scoring is pretty primitive,  and there is an obvious one-to-one map that can be done from the current system to a renown system, so this seems like a snap...\r\n\r\nThings that should get you renown that you haven\'t listed:\r\n\r\n 1) Living through 1K turns.\r\n\r\nPotential problems:\r\n\r\nRenown for killing a big beast might be problematic, as one can easily get into a state when any given beast is not a problem to kill.  Might want to have an exponential back off on this reward.\r\n\r\nRenown penatlies for killing folk in one\'s own clan also seem appropriate.','2001-07-10 14:43:28');
