INSERT INTO messages VALUES (2203,2120,3,2189,1,'Rizen','couple of thoughts','1) you\'ve not played dE before, this is evident or you might understand renown a little better. not a rip on you, just a knowledge factor.\r\n\r\n2) yes, scoring by renown is more complex, but i think also more interesting. i think you agree.\r\n\r\n3) living an amount of time has no grounds for renown what-so-ever unless you\'ve lived beyond expectations. for instance, in dE if you were to live past 70 years old, you\'d be very rare and might earn a small amount of renown for that. in SotF terms you\'d have to live past 100,000 turns or perhaps even more to gain any renown for age.\r\n\r\n4) renown would only be gained for mutated beasties...and perhaps you\'re right...perhaps you\'d only gain renown once for killing a specific type of beast. however, i\'m pretty certain you haven\'t killed all of the beasts in SotF yet. and if you (by some imaginable luck) have, i can certainly add more...cuz there\'s lots of beasts from the dE world that haven\'t made the migration yet.\r\n\r\n5) there should not be renown penalties for killing someone in your own clan. don\'t confuse renown with nobility. you can become just as famous by bad acts as with good.\r\n\r\ni must say that i like this dicussion. i think all of you are correct in saying it needs to be discussed further and details hammered out.','2001-07-10 16:51:13');
