INSERT INTO messages VALUES (2520,2520,3,0,1,'Rizen','Hurried Motion: Renown','Ok, unless there is mega offense to this motion, I\'m going to carry it out right quick. The reason being, I\'ve already brought it up and there was much discussion, and I believe that most of it was positive.\r\n\r\n<li>Renown will determine winner.\r\n<li>1 point of renown will be added for each unique deed.\r\n<li>deeds may not be repeated (hence they are unique).\r\n<li>deeds are: kill a vim dawg, kill slender, complete quest #34\r\n<li>renown does not count until you\'ve told your story, and the story must spread, therefore you must be good at troubadour. \r\n\r\nthe super cool thing is that this will add a storytelling aspect to the game. you will actually need to write a story about your adventure.','2001-07-16 14:43:26');
INSERT INTO messages VALUES (2521,2520,3,2520,5,'Racer X','Kill Slender?','Quest #34? Kill Slender? And what about the other animals that are dangerous?','2001-07-16 14:45:10');
INSERT INTO messages VALUES (2522,2520,3,2521,1,'Rizen','those were examples','\n --- (Edited at Mon Jul 16 14:55:54 2001) --- \n\nthink outside the box....\r\n\r\nkill vim dawg, wild boar, danbury pauncher, etc\r\nkill slender, rizen, bishop, dinsdale, and 400 renown for killing racer x\r\ncomplete quest #1, #2, #3, #4, #5\r\n\r\n\r\n//edit: note that the killing of players will still get you in trouble with the law. in fact, i may have to add more bad effects specifically to outweight the renown gained by killing people.\r\n\r\nalso, we can add other methods of gaining renown later. for instance, we could add in a new quests system for advanced renown-based quests.','2001-07-16 14:52:34');
