INSERT INTO messages VALUES (2635,2635,3,0,447,'Slender','Renown equation','I\'d stay away from multipliers if I were you.  Multipliers can get out of hand fast, and they are hard to reign in, or jigger around.\r\n\r\nWe saw this a lot in the development of last game I worked on.\r\n\r\nI\'d say go with a linear bonus based on remown... one renown, for instance, could be worth 2500 moves.\r\n\r\nAlso, I\'d suggest bumping all the renown numbers by 100.  (and of course scaling down the bonus from the last paragraph)  \r\n\r\nThis makes it possible (later on) and more reasonable to gain different _amounts_ of renown for different things.\r\n\r\nKill a rat?  50 renown.\r\n\r\nKill a daunberry pauncher? 1000 renown.\r\n\r\nKill Slender when he doesn\'t know that alphaprime is vulnerable? 1 renown.','2001-07-18 13:17:30');
INSERT INTO messages VALUES (2636,2636,1,0,447,'Slender','Renown descriptions...','in character \"summaries\" are a little on the ugly side.  \r\n\r\nPlease consider adding a level of indirection to the display, so that we have to click through a \"renown\" link to get all the gorey details of what a character has done...','2001-07-18 13:21:06');
INSERT INTO messages VALUES (2637,2635,3,2635,5,'Racer X','Haha..','You\'re still bitter, aren\'t you?!\r\n\r\nAnd I really don\'t know about the linear bonus. I\'ll leave that to the others.\r\nBut your idea about large amounts of renown is kind of unreal.. This is supposed to be like a sample of dE, and in dE, renown is hard to come by. I don\'t think we want to just hand it out in buckets to people.\r\n\r\nJust what I think! We\'ll see about the others.','2001-07-18 13:47:15');
