INSERT INTO messages VALUES (2643,2635,3,2639,1,'Rizen','my thoughts','1) let\'s see what everyone else has to say about multipliers vs linear adjustments. i really don\'t care either way.\r\n\r\n2) the idea of 100 and 1.00 are irrelevant. everything you can currently do in the game is worth 1 renown, and that\'s the way it should be. in the future i\'ll add a more detailed quest system where the quest prize is renown based, and those deeds (quests) will be worth more than 1 renown. yes i realize that killing a rat isn\'t the same as killing a crimson terror, but in the end, what does it matter since everything is equal?\r\n\r\nthere is no difference between rat=0 + terror=1 & rat=1 + terror=1 since everybody has the same chances at everything.','2001-07-18 17:34:58');
INSERT INTO messages VALUES (2644,2635,3,2635,15,'Fradam','but','\n --- (Edited at Wed Jul 18 17:44:02 2001) --- \n\nthat defeats the whole purpose slender\r\n\r\ni agree with you that the multiplying will get out of hand (if you look at current rankings, you can see that already)\r\n\r\nthe whole drive behind this, was to get away from people scavenging for 100k turns and turning into a mutated radiated beast\r\n\r\nby reducing renown to simply \"2500 moves\", it means you can go back to scavenging\r\n\r\ni mean, dins currently has highest renown on 34, add that by your equation his current turns, and you can see you\'d only have to scavenge for 102944 turns before overtaking him\r\n\r\nand thats without renown\r\n\r\nof which you have 24\r\n\r\nif you\'re going to make a motion out of this, i would vote no to what you\'ve proposed\r\n\r\n','2001-07-18 17:42:58');
