INSERT INTO messages VALUES (2684,2678,3,2682,1,'Rizen','dins is right','if you do it the way he was talking about, it would automatically diminish over time.\r\n\r\nand yes in the deadEarth world this is called apprentiship. basically, if you want to learn smithing, you go pay your local blacksmith to teach you how, or the doctor for first aid, etc.\r\n\r\nthis would be fairly easy to implement and i\'d be willing to do it if we could work out the mathematics properly.\r\n\r\n100 skill points for $2500? how does that sound?\r\n\r\nperhaps i should first explain the mathematics involved in raising skills in sotf.\r\n\r\nSL = current skill level\r\n\r\n\r\n(SL)*(SL+1)*(SL+2) = skill points to next level\r\n\r\neach time a skill level is achieved, then (SL)*(SL+1)*(SL+2) skill points are removed from the player\'s skill points for that skill.\r\n\r\nthis chart describes how many skill points you need to go up:\r\n\r\n0-1 = 0\r\n1-2 = 6\r\n2-3 = 24\r\n3-4 = 60\r\n4-5 = 120\r\n5-6 = 210\r\n6-7 = 336\r\n7-8 = 504\r\n8-9 = 720\r\n9-10 = 990\r\nand so on.\r\n\r\ntherefore to go from 0 to 10 it would take 2970 skill points, or to apprentice from 0 to 10 would cost you $75,000.\r\n\r\nwhat say you?','2001-07-19 17:16:46');
