INSERT INTO messages VALUES (2975,2822,3,2822,6,'Kurtillius','Well, okay then.','\n --- (Edited at Fri Jul 27 23:52:29 2001) --- \n\nI\'ve noticed in the past you seem guys seem to be against things that make other MUD\'s or MMORPG\'s alot more interesting... does something have to have a POINT to be entertaining? That\'s what you guys are arguing. Well let\'s look at a bigger picture:\r\n\r\nDoes this game ITSELF have a point other than to entertain?\r\n\r\nWhatever. No offence, but I Fradam has never agreed with my ideas anyway. From now on I\'ll get someone else to suggest them.\r\n\r\nI don\'t even LIKE SotF, but I\'m still suggesting things to make it ENTERTAINING. This may NOT have much of a POINT, but it IS FUN. It will add more rivalry and clan loyalty to the game!! So WHAT if it won\'t rocket you up the ladder!??!?! It\'s FUN TO DO, but you guys care more about things that\'ll help you get a better chance of winning, not things that make the game more fun. Don\'t fucking argue with that, because that\'s what you\'re saying, and I give up with this. Fine. Let\'s keep this game as shallow as it is. Let\'s not make it fun. I don\'t pay for it, so I don\'t care! \r\n\r\nGoodnight. Also, I\'m not going to diginify your repsonses with further arguments (at least I\'ll try). Have fun.','2001-07-27 23:30:21');
INSERT INTO messages VALUES (2976,2822,3,2975,15,'Fradam','riiiiiight','<i>Does this game ITSELF have a point other than to entertain? \r\n\r\n</i>\r\n\r\nYes, to get Post-Apoc interest happenin, so more people would get into dE. Do you remember why SotF was created -- what it\'s niche was? To keep people at the site...\r\n\r\n<i>No offence, but I Fradam has never agreed with my ideas anyway. From now on I\'ll get someone else to suggest them. \r\n</i>\r\n\r\nWell, <b>right now</b>, I can\'t really think of any of your ideas (perhaps you could list some that you can remember?), and I can\'t find any on Quidspeak aside from this one.\r\n\r\n<i>I don\'t even LIKE SotF</i>\r\n\r\nYou don\'t? I\'d never have guessed.\r\n\r\n<i>I\'m still suggesting things to make it ENTERTAINING</i>\r\n\r\nGreat to hear, suggestions are good for the soul -- keep em rolling :)\r\n\r\n<i>It will add more rivalry and clan loyalty to the game!! </i>\r\n\r\nYou know something? I don\'t think a <b>single person</b> thusfar has said something to the cotrary to this.\r\n\r\n<i>So WHAT if it won\'t rocket you up the ladder!??!?! It\'s FUN TO DO, but you guys care more about things that\'ll help you get a better chance of winning, not things that make the game more fun. Don\'t fucking argue with that</i>\r\n\r\nActually, I will argue with that. When you RP, do you get attached to characters? I would sttate, that for all good players, that over tiem, you develop a certain attachment to the character you play, and thats one of the reasons why your own personal survival skills are transposed onto the character you\'re RP-ing.\r\n\r\nSame thign with SotF. I hear Racer\'s point about the only bad point to dying being losing your items -- and I dispute it. I say, the longer you\'ve played a particular character (just by the fact it has survived), says something of it, and of what <b>you</b> have made of <b>it</b>.\r\n\r\nYou think I wanna throw away a character that has a +7 to combat, +12 to senses and +14 to stealth, just so Racer and Dins have something \"fun\" to do in their free time? \r\n\r\nDo you seriously think I\'d like that sort of thing happening on a regular basis?\r\n\r\nPersonally, I don\'t see the <b>fun</b> in that. Do you? Do you enjoy building up a cool character, going to bed thinking he\'s cool, waking up to your cool character being dead?\r\n\r\nGameplay that affects ladder positions, I can easily deal with... stating that <b>any of us</b> would be against an idea purely for that reason is pure sophistry, and <b>you know it</b>.\r\n\r\n<i>you guys care more about things that\'ll help you get a better chance of winning, not things that make the game more fun</i>\r\n\r\nOh really?? Oh <b>REALLY</b>?? Have you lost your sense of memory or something?\r\n\r\nCast your mind to January, the Daily Killer, and a Top 10 that comprised purely of Quidders. Well, nearly all of it. Do you remember what all went on??\r\n\r\nDo you remember the newbie rule that came in place?!? I cared about that! I had sooooo much fun then! I\'d walk over everyone! LOL! taking out that rule, and stating that Quidders couldn;\'t attack newbies effectively ruined my sense of fun!\r\n\r\nBut I didn\'t sit around griping about it, complaining and whinging. I went ahead, and started an Issues board, and got support of other people... Quid was a bit more alive then, and they were all together and as one that issue.\r\n\r\nWhat happened? Those rules were changed, and my sense of fun returned.\r\n\r\nDid I press that all so that I would win!? NO! I did it so I would get more out of this game and have more fun! I haven\'t won once since that first month, and it\'ll always be the most fun for me! =)\r\n\r\n<i>Fine. Let\'s keep this game as shallow as it is. Let\'s not make it fun. I don\'t pay for it, so I don\'t care! </i>\r\n\r\nKurt. There are about 4-5 people who play this game from my observations that keep playing after they\'ve died. Do you <b>really</b> think Clan Wars, between 3 of em (2 of which are on the same side), will add <b>any</b> depth to the game?\r\n\r\nI really don\'t get you sometimes... you don\'t play this game at all... yet, you still have the gall to make comments about it not being fun? Sarcasm don\'t help you much either, BTW.\r\n\r\n<i>Also, I\'m not going to diginify your repsonses with further arguments</i>\r\n\r\nThat\'s cool with me -- it just lets me know you agreed with everything I said :)','2001-07-28 03:37:54');
