INSERT INTO messages VALUES (3083,3044,1,3053,15,'Fradam','well','\n --- (Edited at Wed Aug  1 03:11:27 2001) --- \n\nrizen wont give us numbers on damage\r\n\r\nbut from what we\'ve ascertained, your skills are in the form of xd6 .. x being your skill\r\n\r\ntherefore, a 15 in combat, means you roll 15d6\r\n\r\nif you\'re taking on a snake, which has a 4 in combat.. means it rolls a 4d6\r\n\r\nso your 15d6 rolls agaisnt his 4d6, and if the difference is greater than a certain proportion, you might get to summon the god of sodomy on some poor soul.. or strike thunder.. etc etc.. but so as long you beat their roll, you\'ll win :)\r\n\r\nthen comes in damage -- we have no numbers on that, but i am quite thinking that armor rating comes into play here... if it\'s above a certain value compared to the incoming damage, it can either either prevent some/all of the damage, else it will prevent none\r\n\r\nthis is in fact a simplified system\r\n\r\nthe real system, has different skills for different types of weapons (e.g. melee weapons, bladed weapons, hanguns etc) as it should be, and can be found at <a href = \"http://www.deadearth.com\">http://www.deadearth.com</a>','2001-08-01 03:11:09');
