INSERT INTO messages VALUES (3089,3089,1,0,969,'shlominus','toughts and suggestions (long)','\n --- (Edited at Wed Aug  1 04:29:34 2001) --- \n\nwell, after my first month i would like to post my impressions and a few suggestions.\r\nvery nice webbased game, one of the best i have seen so far actually. the 5 turns/10 minutes feature as free play is a nice idea. documentation is a little vague on a many subjects, so you have to find out most things by yourself. but thats part of any game. once you get into it everything runs along smoothly. the gossip feature is pure genius, though with a lot of deeds done your creativity is really put to the test. most people write stuff thats really funny to read, which adds a lot of atmosphere. the few number of players active on the other hand limits interaction of characters somewhat. i only met 1 other guy online (who gave me some nice stuff and helped me a lot, thanks again, racer X. and i wont try to rob you again. at least not while you are online :D), so that was about it. i think with more active people that might be different, but with only the pros playing it is a little intimidating for a newb. to end the thoughts and get to the suggestions, it is a fun game that needs more europeans. :P\r\n\r\nnow for some possible suggestions.\r\nwinning: there could be 2 different winners every month, an overall winner and a freegame-winner. the freegame winner only gets the free month. i might paytoplay but not before i saw all the features. with the possibility of winning a free month(which every player should only be able to win once), newbies have more incentive to play and free players have opponents of their own level.\r\n\r\nmonsters: there need to be more mid-level monsters, after you killed all the basic ones you are still not strong enough to tackle the bigger beasties.\r\n\r\nearning money: more skills should be able to generate income. especially for townbound characters. doctors could practice their skills for money. troubadours should earn something for simple gossip, domestic might allow creation of some basic items out of other material.\r\nthat way you could have characters other than fighters or thiefs (fighter/thiefs most likely).\r\n\r\ninactive players: some players stop moving once they are in the lead. there should be a greater chance for random events here to discourage that. th most popular should be \"get thrown out of hotel\" for whatever reason. ;) hiding in hotels is too powerful, therefore not in the spirit of the game. survival is supposed to be a challenge.\r\n\r\nshopping: goods in the shops should change over time. maybe they do, but i didnt notice. it seemed to me, that every shop has the same things all the time.\r\n\r\nage and skill: the advantages in skill are way too much. nobody in his right mind would start a young character. which is unrealistic of course. in the enviroment of the game few people would even reach 60. but in the game they are most powwerful. maybe skills should be broken down into physical(young people are better), like combat, stealth or hork and learned skills(old people are better), like beastlore, tracking or first aid. that might do the trick and add some balance. maybe then we would see some young heroes. and characterv creation could be changed as well. you get basic stats based on your age, then you get  a set number of bonus points to divide. no more rolling till you get a good character.\r\n\r\nrenown and deeds: why the hell do you keep done deeds and renown fter death. its friendly, but not really realistic. i admit it, i made a fighter, killed the beasties. then i made a troubadour, told the stories. voila, speed renown. you should start over from scratch every time you die. that would be tougher, but gaining great renown would really be an accomplishment then. and winning much harder, as competition would be more tougher as well.\r\n\r\nwell, thats all i can think of for now. oh, and i need to work as well. :)\r\ni am looking forward to some replies.\r\ncya all\r\n\r\nshlominus\r\n\r\nps: man, i have too much time on my hands. :)\r\n','2001-08-01 04:23:41');
