INSERT INTO messages VALUES (3096,3089,1,3089,1,'Rizen','reply and consideration','free-players are considered dogs and therefore shall not have an opportunity to win (unless they work really really really hard).\r\n\r\nagreed about mid-level monsters. there are many mutant creatures in the deadEarth world that have not yet bet converted to the SotF world. i\'ll have to work on expanding that.\r\n\r\nthere will be more skills-driven occupations for in-town folk coming shortly.\r\n\r\nthe event to throw someone out of a rented room is a good idea. i\'ll look into that. as far as players becoming inactive when they get into the lead, you need not worry about that as you\'ve not been in the lead. if they are inactive, find them and kill them. even people in rented rooms are vulnerable if you look hard enough.\r\n\r\nsotf is a real economy system. the stores all have their own unique inventory. the problem you saw is that if someone finds an item of great value at a market or some other shop, they snatch it up right away. therefore it looks like the items in the shops are all the same. this month there is a much greater variety of shops on the map, i think you\'ll find it\'s greatly different than last month.\r\n\r\nthere is definite tweaking that needs to happen to the age system. i\'ve made some of those tweaks already at the beginning of this month. i\'ll take a look at your idea as well.\r\n\r\nyes renown staying with your character between deaths is completely unrealistic, but it\'s also a way of letting people keep something of their character between deaths. in almost every online game you\'ll find something completely unrealistic about death. that\'s because people wouldn\'t want to play for very long if they had to start from scratch every single time. i\'m actually considering letting people keep more things between deaths.\r\n\r\nthanks for your comments (both good and bad).','2001-08-01 09:14:15');
