INSERT INTO messages VALUES (3167,3098,3,3098,8,'randomsyllable','OOC: suggestions','\n --- (Edited at Thu Aug  2 19:56:21 2001) --- \n\n --- (Edited at Thu Aug  2 19:55:24 2001) --- \r\n\r\nHmmm...as one of those damn non-ptp types I probably have a bias. Oh well.\r\n\r\nHere goes:\r\n\r\nThe main problem as I see it is that there is very little growth. (re: How to attract more players) As growth will most likely lead to increased ptp, it is the financial base. (I know you said this, but I want to put my thoughts in order)\r\n\r\nSo. Problems(sort of)\r\n\r\nAs I see it. There is an incentive to ptp. You have to to win. However, the mickey for winning is not large enough to promote ptp. Effectively getting your money back will not promote continued use, unless the game evolves. Therefore I must suggest (gasp) falling back on the evercrack principle. Soft is based of deadEarth. Too many people have it the other way around. The real money on a one purchase basis is the dE rulebook.\r\n\r\nI think the target is wrong. Right now, only limited word of mouth and searching brings up either dE or SotF. It needs to be referenced more so that third party systems take up the selling aspect. Personally, I dont think there is enough buzz to get attention.\r\n\r\nThe other thing is that thanks largely to things like EverQuest or AO etc., there is little in the way of a target audience. Hardcore roleplayers who enjoy dE may be turned off by the lack of true interaction and faith to the rules. Conversely, for the casual player, there isnt enough shiny coating. There are no visuals to speak of, every character is limited to the same principles, and as skill evolve through use theres no way to \"level up\" skills through steroetypical means. While this *is* more realistic, it is also not as simple or visceral a concept as other developer-published MMORPGs. This lack of a leveling mechanism may push away people who get bored with the idea of repeating an action until a skill increases, or dying an restarting.\r\n\r\nThe point is that SotF *has* freeplay. Most online games are only ptp. There needs to be an eighties shareware mentality in which ptp is more like supporting the creators for a good product than for the opportunity to play.\r\n\r\nFinally, there is no real \"multiplayer\" experience. Right now, the game plays more like Archmage, 2303 etc. This is because there is no cooperative aspect. Those games *are* free however, which poses a problem. The comparision sinks the ptp aspect here.\r\n\r\n\r\nNow my irrational and badly worded sugested solutions:\r\n\r\nFirst, the \"Everquest\" thing above. Brutally advertise the dE game. With the purchase of the rulebook comes unlimitd access to \"Quid 1\" (Name forthcoming) this is not Quidnunc, merely i dont know what to call it. The idea being that if you buy the book, you are already a member of an \"elite\" group. Take away the elevation to quid as a prize, and insted have an evolving award. Each \"victory\" leads to another level of prestige. Eventually, you come to a point where to advance you must be voted into Quid by its members. Thereby, Quid is still the pinnacle. Award each level its own victory conditions and winner. This will increase the code, im aware, but it would provide challenge of a sorts. For example, the ground level is the turns/renown thing. The second level is highest total skills (add the skills up, take taht number). Stuff like that. Make it at least different. The second part is have different clans for different levels. Maybe you can only be in the Family or FDP at the start (I think they were tradtionally the \"biigest\") As you advance, more clans become available. Maybe flesh out the rads to have names - then as you advance, you start being hit by wierder rads, or meet new creatures. A lot like an RPG would send tougher enemies.\r\n\r\n*breath*\r\n\r\nNext, change the deadEarth site. I only say this because if it were updated and fleshed out it would be more attractive. That would in trun possibly entice people to either buy the game or play SotF. I dont know - just a suggestion.\r\nOn that site bring back the clans and possily karma in some form and such. That way, SotF players who care can go and find the ongoing history of these things and with troubadour and the like, possibly even read about the greater players. Maybe itll encourage them to try the source (read: buy the game). Conversely, rpers will possibly play SotF knowing theres is a solid culture behind it.\r\n\r\nFinally. Let the people pretrend they\'re original. Let tham have a bio page, maybe even create/dl a pic for char. Stuff like that. The more they can personalize the game, the more attractive it may come. As well, if a message board can do it SotF should be able to. As well, it means that the persona in dE or SotF is more easily ported from one to the other, if only in a picture.\r\n\r\n(Something I forgot)\r\n\r\nI don\'t know how, and I realise how hard this would be, but try to get a paty-type thing happening. Gamers congregate, if only to boast and mock. Shouting doesn\'t cut it. If there were some sort of \"contest of skills\" type thing with blow-by-blow commentary, it would provide fodder for talk. Allow people to take on a Crimson Terror together. That sort of thing. (That be the edit)\r\n\r\n\r\nThats all. Sorry it\'s so long. It\'s what I think, no matter how odd/outright stupid.\r\n\r\n\r\nJust some thoughts','2001-08-02 19:50:51');
INSERT INTO messages VALUES (3168,3098,3,3167,10,'Bishop','what i think...','i think that was great...\r\njust to add a spin to randoms words...\r\n\r\ni like the idea of steps in winning, i mean, it is an incentive to keep playing and PTPing.\r\nPerhaps there isnt just one table to win on, i mean as it is us quidders are going to dominate and dominate and dominate.  But what if there are different \"victory conditions\" - Highest renown/most turns spent/Highest natural (non radiated) increase in skills/im sure you can think of more.\r\n\r\nEach person can win <i>one</i> of these victories and gets a somewhat lesser prize.  There is then a ultimate winner who gets the bells and whistles.  Each person can win each victory condition only once until all have been completed.  Then its up for a vote (which by after x monthswould be purely ceremony) to induct or reject a new quidder.\r\nThe whole way through you start to get perks of ptp as random has said.\r\nThen to receive ultimate PTP perks you must either win the ultimate game or actually PTP -\r\ncare must be taken though as not to give the quasiPTP (in a ability sense) too many perks so as not to actually ptp.\r\n\r\nWith a little editing and stuff i think random is on to something.','2001-08-02 21:28:36');
