INSERT INTO messages VALUES (3240,3189,4,3237,969,'shlominus','re: huh?','yes, just to appease me. oh god. an interesting way to approach the problem, dont you think? its a bug, gameplay is hampered by it. greatly. not only for me, but for everybody else as well (i suppose, or am i the only one unable to kill them? last turn nobody could kill spider, if i am correct). \r\n\r\nand even if it did apply only to me (which i am sure of is not the case), then it hampers gameplay a lot. deeds and renown are a very important part to do well in this game, so if people are unable to do deeds and collect renown for them, then they cant play properly. i thought it would be obvious that being invulnerable to other players has a great effect in a game of survival. you seem to disagree, to you i seem to be the only one that cares about that. well, it has been posted twice before (by dinsdale and racer x), making it 5 occurances with my 3 encounters. a bug that has a great effect and happens quite often is a major issue.\r\n\r\nyou will probably only understand that after you encountered the bug yourself a couple of times. i just hope the people able to do anything about it view the situation a little different. and if not, too bad.\r\n\r\n','2001-08-05 23:49:59');
