INSERT INTO messages VALUES (3329,3329,1,0,19,'Dinsdale','CNET troubles....','I tried to post THIS message on CNET, but it keeps saying there\'s an error. You guys can try to copy and paste to see if it works for you or not. Sign my name or yours, who cares. That is, if you think it\'s worth it.\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nIn this world, the goal is to SURVIVE. It takes place in 2024, after world war 3, which was a nuclear disaster that rocked the whole world. In order to survive, you\'ll need alot of items, (there has to be over 250 different items, not including food) decent skills in different areas, many radiations that can boost skill levels, and ALOT of luck.) There is great player interaction. You can use the in game messenger, or use the neat ICQ feature that the game redirects you to. Also, you can steal and kill other players. Though, while killing or stealing, you may be hit by an affinity if the player you torment sits in a town. Some towns have affinities which can either jail you, or kill you for things like having killed other players, stealing from others, and for being a mutant, which is having lots of radiations, whether they be skill boosting or skill subtracting. The items in the game include a football helmet, a 50 calibre rifle, an assortment of body armors, (types 1-4, with vests for 1 2 and 3) pit bulls, and other animals that will help you in certain skills, and also, there are things like lighters and soap and toilet paper.(no, you don\'t actually need to go to the bathroom in the game. Also, watch out for poisons in the food that you eat. It can kill...There is a vast assortment of skills in this game, such as tracking (for tracking your prey to hunt, which is neede to survive) Combat (to be able to win fights; attacking beasts, and other players, as well as fending off other player attacks) troubadour (to gain recognition ((renown)) for all the feats you accomplish, such as quests and killing of other players. This helps you move up in the rankings) senses (HElps you to find things by scavenging, and protect against being stolen from.) stealth (helps you to hide from other players in hope that they won\'t find you, and won\'t be able to attack/steal from you.) hork (ability to steal from others) haggle (ability to get higher prices for items you sell, as well as lower prices for items you buy.) navigate (so you don\'t get lost and move in the wrong direction) beast lore (to know the stats of animals that you track, like the combats or armor rating, or hit points) first aid (to heal wounds inflicted by anything that may harms you. Believe me, lots of things can harm you....) Domestics (to turn the animals you hunt and kill into food.) That concludes my explanation. I\'ll cap it off by saying it\'s a great game, even without paying, but paying makes it a literal 10 times better. Also, SotF is just a spinoff of the real deadEarth game. It\'s a traditional pen and paper RPG following the lines of Dungeons and Dragons tm  and Vampire:the masquerade. tm  Only deadEarth (dE as most call it) is much more realistic and entertaining. Also, the post apocalyptic setting gives you alot of storyline to work with. Visit the site at www.deadearth.com to read about it.\r\n\r\n--Dinsdale--','2001-08-11 21:54:51');
