INSERT INTO messages VALUES (3376,3325,5,3373,969,'shlominus','no biggie, BUT...','i dont consider playing with a ptp account a challenge. and i think a game like this should feel like a challenge. when i play legends of might and magic, i only use armor and powerful weapons against better players. when i play newbies or players of equal skill, i use my sword and no armor. woulndt be fun otherwise. the same applies here. like i said in a previous post, its only a question of how much time one is willing to dedicate, if you want to win. there shouldnt be unlimited moves, for nobody. there shouold be another way to make ptp worth it. unlimited moves take the bite out of the whole game. i really enjoyed playing only a few turns at a time. that way you need to play, set short term goals and make the best of what you got. hey, that sounds like a good representation of survival. even so i managed to get almost all equipment(actually i think i had everything worth haveing, unless there are a few items i dont know of). but it was challenging and exciting, now i have to start over again and its going to be hard work, if i had a ptp account, it wouldnt mean anything at all. my renown is still there, my inventory would be full in no time and i would be bloody rich again. so i was killed, big deal. next time ill camp at a radiation site and get the highest combat skill, then the bastard will pay. nah, i prefer my few turns at a time, ptp as it is now would bore me to death. and the goal of the game is survival, isnt it? maybe there should be some real threat out there. ;)','2001-08-13 11:50:52');
