INSERT INTO messages VALUES (3662,3648,3,3652,13,'tera','Bonuses','OK maybe people don\'t realize that there are bonuses to being non-newbies. You mentioned the geneticist and the trade depot. Let\'s expand on that. Maybe there needs to be more than one geneticist. And maybe there needs to be cooler items at the trade depots. And these things need to be advertised in game so that newbies hear about them and think \"wow that\'s cool. I want it.\" By advertising, I mean have a list of some equipment and post the stats on it. Like a Pee-Wee hacksaw. It adds 10 to combat and 10 to hide because it\'s really sharp and small. But it doesn\'t do as much damage as Big Badass hacksaw because that is bigger and it gets a negative to hide. (Just made up examples off the top of my head.) \r\nQuidders get to vote on the rules, too. Maybe have that advertised in game. When a change is made because of the Quidders post it on a message-type board or something. That might generate an interest in winning. And if the top person cannot be a newbie, then it might lite a fire under people to get past the newbie status.\r\nOther suggestions please.','2001-08-24 15:31:05');
