INSERT INTO messages VALUES (3715,3715,1,0,855,'Chemical Halo','hey Rizen','heres an idea for ya... get the permision first though... \r\n\r\nAmbrosia Software is makeing an RPG Engine for MAC and PC (one of two programs by them for both platforms) with the cooperation of Beenox (maybe youve heard of them?)\r\n the name of the engine is called ColdStone\r\n(www.ambrosiaSW.com under the \"whats comming\" section\")\r\n\r\nim thinking maybe you could somehow make SOTF into an RPG like that... and somehow make it so that we could play multiplayer online, like a charicter ladder like we have now, just click a button and it will upload the charicter info (the game will, not the person) to your database.  and we can come on here for the old style and check the ladder. aswell as the boards.\r\n\r\nBTW, the game they made w/ it already  is available for download at the Ambrosia Software website if anyone wants to take a looksee :) its called Pillars of Garendall. A full version can be either downloaded or purchased on CD. (you have to pay for them though, only 25 bucks but thats not bad considering they mostly make shareware and all thier prices are 25 bucks.) theres a free demo however that you can get there to.\r\n\r\nya know, just incase you were thinking of adding abit more interactivity with the game...','2001-08-31 09:22:54');
