INSERT INTO messages VALUES (4368,4367,1,4367,969,'shlominus','my vote (+suggestions)','of the 3 possibilities, i would choose a.\r\n\r\nbut the most important part that needs work is the economic system. there are ways of generating an unlimited amount of money if you know how to do it (no, i wont tell anyone, not even chemical halo :P).\r\n\r\nthings that need to be changed about it:\r\n1) a trader should never buy an item for more money than you paid him for it, no matter how high your haggle skill (i mean, how are they going to make a profit like that?)\r\n2) there should be \"virtual customers\". if only the players buy and sell stuff, then sooner or later all good items will be sold and all shops will be full of gubbinz that has been dumped there by the players. therefore all shops should sell a certain percentage (is that correct?) of their goods every day (or week) to \"virtual customers\"=npcs. that means that shops will have interesting items to sell, even at the end of a playing month(and even more importantly, money to buy expensive items from the players). to make it easier (i have no knowledge of coding or programming), all shops could set to a default setting every week. tehy get their basic goods and a set amount of money (depending on kind of shop and size of the city its located in).\r\n\r\nthats all for now. i will surely think of a few other things. but my habit of writing longwinded posts struck again. ;)','2001-11-17 17:10:52');
