INSERT INTO messages VALUES (4419,4412,1,4412,1075,'Raptor','Rizen','Would it possible to employ some sort of chase or tracking skill when trying to follow another player. Just a thought. \r\n\r\nAlso, I agree with shlominus that you should be able to increase your skills much faster through practice. The game is weighted a little too strongly towards rads. Some rads don\'t make much sense. Just becasue I get irradiated, all of a sudden I can sew better. Senses, Combat, Stealth. Skills like those I can see being affected by rads. But some others just don\'t seem to fit.','2001-11-27 09:13:08');
INSERT INTO messages VALUES (4420,4367,1,4406,1175,'Dojie','Skills','Combat in particular needs to be easier to increase.  I like the apprenticeships, and I would be fine with having an apprenticeship for combat, but I think you should be able to increase them faster through practice.  \r\n\r\nOne other change I\'d like to see.  If someone tries to kill me or steal from me, I would like to be able to kill them without it counting as a murder for affinities.\r\n\r\nI really like the quests - I would like to see more of them.','2001-11-27 11:05:42');
