INSERT INTO messages VALUES (4635,4627,1,4633,969,'shlominus','hm... (loooooong)','you dont HAVE to be a fighter, but chances are people are going to kill you a lot then. because a), they get renown and b), they get your stuff.\r\n\r\nthe game mechanics make people kill each other. having a lot of money at the end of the game may be a nice aim for you, but it wont win you the game.\r\n\r\nrizen would have to change the whole game to get less player-to-player violence. right now itnot a roleplaying game (and i dont think it was intended that way, roleplaying games cant be \"won\"), but it could evolve into one.\r\n\r\nmy most radical idea into that direction would be some kind of party or \"buddy\"-system. you could join forces with several people, gaining a deed just like from killing them. you could still attack them, but would get a penalty to your renown. \"buddies\" should be able to transfer items more easely(cause dropping and scavenging sucks. theoretically you might even lose that nice type4 armor, because the sweeperbot chose excactly that moment of drop/scavenge to wipe the square) and might even get boni if they hunted or attacked while in the same square. that way you could kill bigger beasties, be protected from random attacks (you thought yourself a goner, but raptor pulls you out of the quicksand with a rope) and most important of all, you dont have to kill everyone you meet. :)\r\n\r\nin such a system, a scavenge/trader-type character would benefit a group, while being protected from the fighter characters.\r\n\r\ni know its radical, but it shouldnt be too hard to code. simply add another option to the player interaction menu, join forces? or something like that. the other player would have to accept of course. from that moment on, whenever something happens to a player, a check is made if a teammate is in the same square. if there is one, he might get a bonus for some skills (maybe highest skill in group/5 as a bonus), he could eat the others food instead of starving and so forth.\r\n\r\ntell me what you think.\r\n\r\n','2001-12-18 11:39:27');
