INSERT INTO messages VALUES (4655,4655,5,0,2,'lynx','Survival of the Fittest','   I was thinking to myself the other day, and I cant get over the fact that this world we live\r\nin has changed in such a way that no one could imagine. Just nine years ago I was living very comfortably in my home, with my beutiful family, and teaching history class at the local high school. In just nine years, the world has taken an almost 180 degree turn in time. I am currently walking down the streets of Greenwood, and it looks as it would have some 200 years ago. Local armor and weapon stores, rarely any vehicals, and only a faint of technology anywere. \r\n\r\n\r\nIts a common thing these days to hear about a person being killed for his jacket, or his copy of \"Kama Sutra\", and no one does anything about it. I can remember the days when two people would get into a small fist fight and the law had to get involved. A person doesnt dare leave the house without a weapon of sort, and armor. \r\n\r\n\r\n  And dont let me forget the nuclear radiation the war has left us with. Very few people got off lucky, and still look like a person- a human, what ever you consider normal. Im about the same as an average person in this horrible world. I have a few radiations now which could get me killed or inlisted into some ungodly service in some parts of the world. Im am slowly begining to glow the color magenta, but hey I can live with that when I look down the street and see a man I use to know growing spike-like things on his back.\r\n\r\n\r\nMany people are starting to call this planet deadEarth-The place were people are not\r\nliving, just mearly staying alive-and I may add that even that is hard to do.\r\n','2001-12-21 20:26:33');
